AIM:  
	To automate the build and packaging of a Java application using Apache Maven.  

ALGORITHM:  
	Step 1: Create a simple Java Maven project containing the required files such as pom.xml, App.java, and AppTest.java. 
	Step 2: Open the project folder in Command Prompt or Terminal. 
	Step 3: Execute the command mvn validate to verify the project structure and dependencies. 
	Step 4: Run the command mvn compile to compile the source code. 
	Step 5: Execute mvn test to run the unit test cases and verify the application functionality. 
	Step 6: Run the command mvn package to package the compiled code and generate the JAR file in the target folder. 
	Step 7: Execute mvn install to install the generated package into the local Maven repository. 
	Step 8: Verify that each Maven command executes successfully and displays BUILD SUCCESS as the output. 

PROGRAM:  
	 APP.JAVA: 

public class App {

    public static String greet() {
        return "Hello, Maven Build Automation!";
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(greet());
    }
}

APPTEST.JAVA 

package com.example;

import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.assertEquals;

public class AppTest {

    @Test
    public void testGreet() {
        assertEquals("Hello, Maven Build Automation!", App.greet());
    }
}


XML

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-demo</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.13.2</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.10.1</version>
                <configuration>
                    <source>17</source>
                    <target>17</target>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>



Maven Command:   
	mvn clean  
	mvn compile 
	mvn test 
	mvn package 


RESULT:  
	Thus, the Maven project was compiled, tests were executed, and the application package was generated successfully.  
